originalText.text: It is too late to reach management by the attendant continued to drive my manual transmission truck to me while the clutch was burning and smoking. First gear is blown out and I will be contacting management and my attorney. The attendant could not understand what I was saying and he said “it stopping smoking”. This garage will be paying for the repairs. If you cannot drive stick shift then you do not accept the car or have the owner drive it. Completely unacceptable, unprofessional and a very costly issue.

originalText.text: 215 East 24th Street New York, NY 10010-3802. Attendant was having trouble inputting my wife's Park whiz reservation. So much so he started punching his desk which alarmed my wife and our daughter. They began to feel unsafe. At that point he stated to just pay directly. My wife asked for a price for 3 hours and he would not give an answer. He said could be $15 or $50. My wife advised she would find another garage and then the attendant CLOSED THE GATE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Obviously, they now feel threatened that, and agitated male has trapped them! My wife then calls the police. Only then did he open up the gates. This employee should be fired immediately. My wife and Daughter were coming from Sloan cancer center, recovering from Brain surgery 3 weeks ago. I'm only thankful this situation did not get physical as that could have been detrimental to my wife's recovery. I doubt this would have happened if I was there. Only cowards threaten females.

originalText.text: They said they lost my check for monthly parking, then I gave them another and before I could cancel the checks, both were cashed and I'm out $300. During the pandemic, we planned to get out of town and the garage was LOCKED! No way to access, nobody answering phones. They also parked our car IN STANDING WATER and it sat there for days. I tried to work it out with the company and they kept promising a refund but it never happened. Never give them your money, they will find a way to scam you.
